    "Summaries can also be tailored to specific user intents, which is particularly challenging when dealing with long-tail user intents.",
    "This difficulty arises because even some of the most advanced LLMs today struggle to accurately recognize and address niche intents, as analyzed and discussed by Bodonhelyi et al. (2024).",
    "The assessment of intent-driven summarization holds significant potential for further research and novel specialized metrics, capturing the semantic adequacy of a summary and user satisfaction.",
    "In this survey, we employ a systematic review approach following the methodology defined by Kitchenham and Charters (2007).",
    "We detail the review methodology in Appendix A."
